      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH computed as the ratio of device NIH to predicate NIH. This QoI is directly tied to the regulatory acceptance criterion. Secondary QoIs (volume-averaged shear stress, exposure time distributions) support mechanistic interpretation. Relevance is confirmed per project requirements."
